default4default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultHow should expenditure on improving safety at level crossings be prioritised in relation to other demands on the rail budget?default&#xa0;default4.1
default&#xa0; 
defaultThis is the most sensitive s
defaultubject area. In an ideal world, public money would be directed at those areas that deliver the greatest benefit to the public – usually known as ‘value for money.’  The industry uses the criteria established in the Health and Safety at Work Act (1974) and 
defaultthe EU Railway safety Directive to determine its safety expenditures – applying the principle of reducing risk ‘so far as is reasonably practicable.’  
default&#xa0;
default4.2
default&#xa0; 
defaultUsing these criteria across the board could lead to some reallocation of resources away from level cros
defaultsings because many of the investments that are being made are not justified on those terms – rather they are made to meet a target of risk reduction, or in some cases simply to enable a particular crossing to be closed. RSSB has produced guidance on decisi
defaulton-making on safety priorities in the industry approved document
default 
defaultT
defaultaking Safe Decisions 
default(RSSB 2008
default)
default which mirrors some of the wording of Network Rail’s certified Safety 
defaultM
defaultanagement System. 
default 
defaultNetwork Rail
default’
defaults decisions and proposals on 
defaultl
defaultevel crossing expenditure
default are
default partly 
defaulta 
defaultrecognition of the public concern which is expressed whenever an accident occurs 
defaultand
default 
defaultalso because the risk comes largely from outside the rail sector, caused by people over whom the railways have no direct control. They are consequently diffi
defaultcult - and expensive - to reach and to influence. 
defaultThe number of trains on the network continues to increase significantly, so as
default the current initiatives continue to produce results and risk is driven down further, it may become more and more difficult to j
defaultustify and implement further improvements to address the 
defaultr
defaultisk
default which will remain
default.  It must be noted that the
default between 
defaultsix 
